Business Brief -- American Express Co.:
   Firm Completes Acquisition
   Of Lifeco Travel Services
Lifeco's 1991 sales totaled about $1.2 billion, mostly
derived from corporate travel customers.
   Lifeco will operate as Lifeco/American Express during a
transition period of a year to 18 months, and customers will
continue to be served by Lifeco representatives. American
Express officials weren't immediately available for comment
about plans beyond the transition period.
   American Express, through its travel-related services
unit, is a leading travel-management company.